What is a Server? ğŸ¤”
A server is a powerful computer ğŸ’ª designed to provide services, data, or programs to other machines, known as clients, within a network. Servers are the gatekeepers, managing requests for anything from web pages ğŸŒ to large-scale applications ğŸ›ï¸.

Client vs. Server ğŸŒŸ
Client ğŸ–¥ï¸: A client device, such as a computer, smartphone ğŸ“±, or tablet, requests resources from a server. For example, when you browse a website, your browser (the client) sends a request to a web server.
Server ğŸ–¥ï¸ğŸ’¾: The server processes client requests and provides the requested resources. For instance, a web server delivers HTML content for web pages, handling user requests in real time.
Server Structure ğŸ—ï¸
Servers consist of both hardware and software components designed to work together seamlessly, enabling efficient management and processing of data.

