Server Operation ğŸ› ï¸
Service Management ğŸ”„: IT admins control which services are active to ensure efficient performance. Load Balancing ğŸ“Š spreads the load across servers, preventing overload on a single machine.

Uptime & Downtime ğŸ•°ï¸
Uptime is a measure of reliability, indicating how long a server remains operational. High uptime is critical for business continuity and customer trust. Redundancy measures, such as backup power supplies âš¡ and RAID configurations, help prevent downtime.

Server Storage Options ğŸ—„ï¸
Local Storage vs. NAS: Local storage offers quick access, while NAS centralizes data management.
